  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Prepare Repository for Open Source Publication\n\nClean up, configure, and document the repository so it's ready for public release on GitHub or similar platforms.\n\nRequirements:\n\nDocumentation\n- Write comprehensive README with: project overview, features, installation, development setup, usage examples, and contribution guidelines\n- Add LICENSE file (choose appropriate license based on project dependencies)\n- Create CONTRIBUTING.md with pull request workflow, coding standards, and testing requirements\n- Add Code of Conduct (e.g., Contributor Covenant)\n- Create CHANGELOG.md documenting all notable changes\n\nCode & Configuration Cleanup\n- Audit for and remove all hardcoded secrets, API keys, tokens, and credentials\n- Ensure .gitignore excludes sensitive files (.env, credentials.json, node_modules, build artifacts)\n- Replace internal/project-specific configurations with placeholder values\n- Remove any personal or company-specific references\n- Verify package.json has correct public metadata (name, repository, author, license)\n\nSecurity Hardening\n- Run npm audit fix to address known vulnerabilities\n- Ensure environment variables are properly documented with .env.example\n- Verify no sensitive data is committed to git history\n\nGit Hygiene\n- Review recent commits for any sensitive information\n- Ensure main branch is clean and represents release-ready state\n- Add .github templates for issues and pull requests\n\nFinal Steps\n- Verify npm run build succeeds\n- Test fresh clone installation process\n- Confirm all links and references work correctly",
